ğŸ‘— Culture & Etiquette
Kazakhstan is a Muslim-majority country, but itâ€™s also very secular and cosmopolitan, especially in Almaty. Dress is generally European-style and relaxed. Just dress modestly if visiting mosques.

Kazakh people are famously hospitable, and a few Russian/Kazakh phrases go a long way, though younger people often speak some English.

